        "authorId" : "bfe6ebf1-cfa7-4758-abb1-9960fa09b194",
        "body" : "In some images, we're running `apt-get upgrade` here also to get upgrades on \"child\" image builds.\r\nMakes sense?",
        "createdAt" : "2017-02-22T20:13:21Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2017-02-24T00:15:34Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "bfe6ebf1-cfa7-4758-abb1-9960fa09b194",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "e2cfdc73-f5ff-41ce-a4ea-959688a1a909",
        "parentId" : "2eedae5c-7efd-4836-972e-e5dba4c07cbd",
        "authorId" : "0adf587c-aaa2-4e47-be0f-a26d4fde14ac",
        "body" : "If a higher layer upgrades packages in a lower layer, the image ends up carrying 2 copies of the package (the outdated version in the lower layer, which is masked by the update). Since we will maintain the base image, we should also be responsible for updating the base as needed.",
        "createdAt" : "2017-02-22T20:52:44Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2017-02-24T00:15:34Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "0adf587c-aaa2-4e47-be0f-a26d4fde14ac",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      }
